Cardio Good Fitness Project

Overview

This project has 3 main parts:

  1. Introduction
  2. Exploratory Data Analysis
    • A) Data Structure Overview
    • B) Univariate Data Analysis
    • C) Multivariate Data Analysis
  3. Conclusion

Introduction

This project is about the analysis of the customers with the treadmill products at Cardio Good Fitness store. The dataset is analyzed to identify the differences of the customers for each product. In the end of the project, we would like to have key of insights and recommendations to help company to target new customers.

Conclusion

  • Based on the observations, TM195 is the most popular treadmill product comparing to TM498 and TM798. Overall, Male population is more likely to buy more treadmill products than female in this dataset. Hence, male tends to use more treadmills, run more miles and more fit than female. This is also because male earns more income than female based on the observation in the dataset, therefore they are able to afford the products.
  • The most customers that buy treadmill products overall are in the age group 15-20 and 20-25. As the age increase, the less people likely to buy treadmill products.
  • Besides, customers that are partnered tends to have more treadmill products than single customers. Based on all the observations, the business can promote and produce more TM195 products, and target more in younger generations.
  • In addition, business can have sales and deals in holidays for TM498 and TM798 products if they would like to sell more of these. Hence, there would be more options for customers to choose.
  • Having appealing commercial advertistments can also attract more customers to use, especially advertisements about couples exercising together, or single customers if business wants to target more for that group. In addition, business can give out deals and sales if they want to target more female and more variety of age groups.
